  {
    "id": "bank-b-q012",
    "type": "mcq",
    "topic": "hardware-memory",
    "subtopic": "storage-units",
    "stem": "1 Gigabyte (GB) is equal to",
    "options": [
      {
        "label": "A",
        "text": "1024 bytes",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "B",
        "text": "1024 KB",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "C",
        "text": "1024 MB",
        "isCorrect": true
      },
      {
        "label": "D",
        "text": "1024 TB",
        "isCorrect": false
      }
    ],
    "answerOptionLabels": [
      "C"
    ],
    "explanation": "The binary ladder steps by 1024 each rung: 1 KB = 1024 bytes, 1 MB = 1024 KB, 1 GB = 1024 MB. Option A (1024 bytes) is the definition of a kilobyte, not a gigabyte, and 1024 TB would be a petabyte, so the only rung that lands on GB is 1024 MB.",
    "source": {
      "file": "Computer Engineering K-Companies Exam - Questions.pdf",
      "exam": "bank",
      "tier": "bank",
      "originalNumber": 13
    },
